<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-21T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="85" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European Advisory
                            Commission/58a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-21T17:00:00-04:00">January
                                    21, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>517. British Embassy informs us that based upon discussions at Moscow and
                            Tehran, British Government desires to propose that the European Advisory
                            Commission set up a special body to study question <pb facs="0175" n="163" xml:id="pg_163"/> of dismemberment of Germany. You are
                            authorized to accept the subject of dismemberment for discussion in the
                            European Advisory Commission in any form the Commissioners may
                            decide.</p>
                        <p>We consider that this subject is already before the Commission under
                            penultimate paragraph, Section B, of U. S. paper on treatment of
                            Germany, referred to the Commission by the Moscow Conference.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>